label: intellectual developmental disorder, autosomal recessive 75, with neuropsychiatric features and variant lissencephaly
immunodeficiency 99 with hypogammaglobulinemia and autoimmune cytopenias
tobacco addiction, susceptibility to
definition: An inherited susceptibility or predisposition to developing nicotine dependence.

label: methylmalonic aciduria and/or homocystinuria, cblD type
definition: An autosomal recessive inborn disorder of cobalamin metabolism caused by biallelic variants in MMADHC. Depending on the type and location of variants in MMADHC, patients may present with methylmalonic aciduria, homocystinuria, or both. MMADHC has been reported to result in the cblD complementation group of cobalamin disorders.

label: glutaric acidemia IIa
definition: Any multiple acyl-CoA dehydrogenase deficiency in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the ETFA gene.

label: glutaric acidemia IIb
definition: Any multiple acyl-CoA dehydrogenase deficiency in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the ETFB gene.

label: glutaric acidemia IIc
definition: Any multiple acyl-CoA dehydrogenase deficiency in which the cause of the disease is a mutation in the ETFDH gene.
